cs.SC, cs.SY, cs.DS, cs.NA, cs.CG 

Reasoning: 
- cs.SC (Symbolic Computation) is the most likely category as the paper proposes a new algorithm for solving differential polynomial systems using multivariate resultant theory, which falls under the scope of symbolic computation. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also likely as the paper deals with ordinary differential polynomial systems, which are commonly used in control theory. 
- cs.DS (Dynamical Systems) is another possible category as the paper deals with systems of differential equations. 
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) is a possible category as the paper discusses the computational complexity of the proposed algorithm. 
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is a less likely category, but still possible as triangular decomposition is a technique used in computational geometry for solving systems of polynomial equations.
